<pb facs="1079231" n="1"/>
<opener><salute><choice><abbr>Illustriss.<hi rend="sup">o</hi>imo</abbr><expan>Illustrissimo</expan></choice> atque <choice><abbr>Celeberr.<hi rend="sup">o</hi>imo</abbr><expan>Celeberrimo</expan></choice> Viro <choice><abbr>Jo:</abbr><expan>Johanni</expan></choice> <rs key="pers_DE-588-118509969" type="person">Bernoullio</rs>
<lb/>Petrus Antonius <rs key="pers_DE-588-102552517" type="person">Michelottus</rs> <abbr>S. P. D.</abbr></salute></opener>
<p><lb/>Hactenus expectavi frustra responsion<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice> ad binas, quas ad
         <lb/>Te, Vir Doctissime, dedi <rs key="brieftag" type="letter">Literas</rs><note type="editorial">Zwischen diesem Brief und dem letzten Brief liegen vier Briefe 000056707, 000056708, 000056709, 000056710 Michelottis. Da Michelotti unten auf die beiden Briefe verweist, die wo es um die Auseinandersetzung mit dem pronewtonianischen Riccati geht, müssten es die letzten beiden Briefe 000056709, 000056710 vom 2. und 30. Mai 1721 sein.</note>, demirorque in pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>sentia
         <lb/>fascicul<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> ex binis mei <rs key="biblio_M3G2JA79" type="biblio">de separatione Fluidor<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> in Corpo<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>re Animali</rs><note type="editorial">Michelotti, Pietro Antonio, De separatione fluidorum in corpore animali dissertatio physico-mechanico-medica, Venetiis (A. &amp; A. Pinelli) 1721. (Digitalisat bei BSB digital). Bibliographie zur Korrespondenz zwischen Johann I Bernoulli und Johann Jakob Scheuchzer.</note> operis exemplaribus compositum nondum
         <lb/>ad vos fuisse perlatum; pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>sertim qu<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> ex Muliere No<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>bilissima Marchione <rs key="GND" type="person">Maria Loaysa Butintrochi</rs> Mediolanen<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>si, ill<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> ips<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> fasciculum<note type="editorial">Was bezeichnet Faszikel hier?</note> ante duos menses <rs key="place_GEO-3173435" type="place">Mediolano</rs>
<lb/><rs key="place_GEO-2661604" type="place">Basileam</rs> fuisse miss<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice>, nuper intellexerim. Mense
         <lb/>pr<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>terito <choice><abbr>Clariss.</abbr><expan>Clarissimus</expan></choice> Filius Tuus <rs key="pers_DE-588-117589144" type="person">Nicolaus</rs> salutem plurimam
         <lb/>tuo nomine, Inclyte Vir, mihi dixit, meque fecit certio<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>rem, meas <rs key="brieftag" type="letter">epistolas</rs><note type="editorial">Es muss um die zwei Briefe 000056709, 000056710 vom 2. und 30. Mai 1721 gehen, in denen Riccati ein Thema ist</note>, in quibus de <choice><abbr>Illustriss.</abbr><expan>Illustrissimi</expan></choice> Viri <rs key="pers_DE-588-119543885" type="person"><choice><abbr>Jac.</abbr><expan>Jacobi</expan></choice> Ric<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>cati</rs> demonstratione quad<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice>, pro veritate corollarii 2<choice><orig><g ref="#ndot">.</g></orig><reg></reg></choice> <choice><abbr>prop.</abbr><expan>propositionis</expan></choice>
<lb/>37 eximii <rs key="biblio_6CP8LL78" type="biblio">libri</rs><note type="editorial">werktag: newtonbhbd auf BEOL und schon für den Platzhalter eingesetzt: Newton, Princ. Math., 1713. Falls die Amsterdamer Ausgabe von 1714 oder eine andere Edition der Principia gemeint ist (vgl. Brief 000056709 vom 2. Mai 1721), müsste das Buch erfasst und geändert werden.</note> <rs key="pers_DE-588-118587544" type="person">Newtoniani</rs> militante, verba feci, ad
         <lb/>Tuas pervenisse manus, itemque spem fecit, te cito ad
         <lb/>me scripturum de illa ipsa demonstratione,
         <lb/>quam nihil aliud esse putas, quam paralogismum
         <lb/>uti loquuntur. Scio me Tibi esse literis meis mult<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice>
         <lb/>admod<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> molestum, verumtamen tua incomparabili
         <lb/>benignitate fretus iterum audeo, Te etiam atque etiam
         <lb/>rogare, ut quamcitissime fieri poterit ad me mittas ra<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>tiones omnes, quibus <choice><sic>convllli</sic><corr>convelli</corr></choice> possit <choice><abbr>Nobiliss.</abbr><expan>Nobilissimi</expan></choice> <rs key="pers_DE-588-119543885" type="person">Riccati</rs> ra<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>tiocinatio, eamque pur<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> put<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> esse paralogismum
         <lb/>demonstrari. Me Tibi, propter maxim<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> quibus
         <lb/>me cumulasti gratiar<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> cumul<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice>, devinctissim<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> esse
       <pb facs="1079232" n="2"/>
<lb/>publice fassus sum semperque quamdiu fuero
         <lb/>fatebor: sin aut<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice> ad hanc me<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> <rs key="brieftag" type="letter">epistolam</rs><note type="editorial">Meint vermutlich den Brief 000056709 vom 30. Mai 1721, wo Riccati und Newton inhaltlich behandelt werden. Michelotti erbat schon im Brief vom 2. Mai eine Rückmeldung Joh. I B.'s zu seinen Ausführungen.</note> quam
         <lb/>primum responderis, omniaque qu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> de vi
         <lb/>mot<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> aqu<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice> per foramen in fundo vasis factum
         <lb/>exilientis generante dici, aut cogitari possunt
         <lb/>adversus <rs key="biblio_6CP8LL78" type="biblio">Corollari<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs><note type="editorial">Meint vermutlich auch die Principia oder einen Teil davon. Überhaupt mit einem tag zu versehen?</note> Newtonian<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice>, de quo supra
         <lb/>dicebam, mecum communicaveris, me Tibi in
         <lb/><choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>ternum obligatissimum habebis.</p> <closer><salute>Vale, Vir <choice><abbr>Ingeniosiss.<hi rend="sup">e</hi></abbr><expan>Ingeniosissime</expan></choice>, mihique respondere atque favere ne dedigneris.</salute>
<dateline>Dab<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> <rs key="place_GEO-3164603" type="place">Venetiis</rs> <choice><abbr>a.</abbr><expan>ante</expan></choice> <choice><abbr>d.</abbr><expan>diem</expan></choice> <date when="1721-07-11">11 Julii 1721.</date></dateline></closer>
<postscript><p><lb/><choice><abbr>Clariss.<hi rend="sup">us</hi></abbr><expan>Clarissimus</expan></choice> Filius tuus <rs key="pers_DE-588-117589144" type="person">Nicolaus</rs> heri una cum Viro
         <lb/><choice><abbr>Ill.<hi rend="sup">o</hi></abbr><expan>Illustrissimo</expan></choice> atque <choice><abbr>Excell.<hi rend="sup">o</hi></abbr><expan>Excellentissimo</expan></choice> <rs key="pers_DE-588-121710742" type="person"><choice><abbr>Jo.</abbr><expan>Johanne</expan></choice> Vezzi</rs><note type="editorial">Vermutlich ist diese Person gemeint, ev. ist die GND-Nummer aber noch zu prüfen.</note> hinc <rs key="place_GEO-3165243" type="place">Trident<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs> versus
         <lb/>discessit ad potand<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> aquam quandam mi<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/>neralem ex fonte Vallis cujusd<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> <hi rend="u"><rs key="place_WEI-disole" type="place">del Sole</rs></hi> appellat<choice><orig><g ref="#ae">æ</g></orig><reg>ae</reg></choice>
         <lb/>prosilientem, redibitque, uti spero, post mens<choice><orig><g ref="#em">ē</g></orig><reg>em</reg></choice>.
         <lb/>Si velis ad ill<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice> dare literas, eas ad me trans<pc type="hyphenation">-</pc>
<lb break="no"/><choice><sic>mitere</sic><corr>mittere</corr></choice> poteris; ego enim citissime illas ipsas
         <lb/>literas mitt<choice><orig><g ref="#am">ā</g></orig><reg>am</reg></choice> <rs key="place_GEO-3165243" type="place">Trident<choice><orig><g ref="#um">ū</g></orig><reg>um</reg></choice></rs><supplied>.</supplied></p></postscript>
